      "body_text": "A man on a donkey in 1635\nThe scent of a flower on a Thursday\nThe sound a candle makes\nA spoon dropped in a cathedral\nFirst breath after swimming underwater\nThe third exhale of a long story\nA child's forgotten birthday wish\nMoonrise viewed from a kitchen window\nThe taste of tap water at 3am\nA door closing behind someone you love\nThe first hour of a snowstorm\nA grandmother's lullaby half-remembered\nCoffee steam on a bathroom mirror\nThe weight of an unopened letter\nFootsteps in an empty hallway\nA postman pausing before knocking\nThe smell of rain on hot pavement\nA letter that arrived eleven days late\nThe last verse of a song nobody sings anymore\nA dog dreaming\nSunday afternoon in a library with no one in it\nA forgotten pocket in a winter coat\nThe quiet between two fireworks\nTea steeping for far too long\nAn old map folded wrong\nThe first cricket of summer\nA stranger's laugh overheard on a train\nA child counting stars out loud\nThe click of a film camera in the next room\nA train whistle at 4am\nThe last page of a book you didn't want to end\nA kettle about to boil\nRain hitting a window at night\nA cat watching traffic from a fourth-floor sill\nThe breath between two lines of poetry\nA balloon caught in a winter tree\nA telephone ringing in a film\nA candle three seconds after blowing out\nThe pause before a joke lands\nA passport lost and then found\nSnow melting on a hat you forgot you were wearing\nRust on a bicycle chain in April\nThe moment before applause\nA pigeon landing on a statue's head\nThe smell of a library book from 1974\nA broken promise, nonetheless kept\nA forgotten umbrella at a wedding\nThe last warm day of September\nA hand waving goodbye through a train window\nA bird flying into a room and out again\nThe taste of your own name said by a stranger\nA childhood pet's name\nThe sound a memory makes when it almost surfaces\nCoffee gone cold on a desk\nA cake baking in an empty house\nAn email sent to exactly the wrong person\nFootprints in wet sand being erased\nA mother calling you home for dinner\nThe shadow of a moth on a lampshade\nA coin spinning on a wooden table\nA subway arriving empty at midnight\nThe warmth of a laptop on your legs\nA doorway that only exists in a dream\nThe echo of a church bell at dusk\nA neighbor practicing piano badly\nAn aunt's kitchen in the summer of 1992\nWind pushing a screen door gently\nA recipe written in pencil on an index card\nA photograph deleted accidentally\nThe weight of words you didn't say\nA puddle reflecting a cloud\nA conversation with your eighteen-year-old self\nThe last letter of a foreign alphabet\nA friend who moved away and stayed away\nDust dancing in a beam of sunlight\nThe kind of silence only cats know\nA freshly-made hotel bed\nThe gap between a breath and a sigh\nThe hum of a refrigerator at night\nA wedding ring left on a bedside table\nA library card from 1987\nA child's drawing held up by a magnet\nA chair that remembers the shape of someone\nThe breeze from a ceiling fan in August\nA grandfather clock ticking in a dark hallway\nThe inside of a snowglobe mid-shake\nAn unpaid utility bill\nThe first frost on grass\nA song stuck in someone else's head\nA book you keep meaning to read\nThe smell of sunscreen on a cold day\nA bowl of cherries in midsummer\nA taxi passing through rain without stopping\nThe sound of a zipper in a quiet room\nA cardboard box with no return address\nAn umbrella on a coat rack in June\nThe taste of homesickness\nA paper crane on a windowsill\nA melody heard only in dreams\nThe moment you realize a page is ending"
    }
